We allow external customers to open tickets within Jira but we do not allow allow Jira to automatically create new users within our system. We handle this by having a single Jira account appear as default reporter when the email is imported.

The problem our customer service representatives have when working these tickets is that they have no idea who the email is from or who it was sent to (other than the Jira account). To resolve this, I created a patch for CreateIssueHandler.java that modifies the recordedFromAddressForAnon method. The modification expands on the "[Created via email received from: ... ]" tag line and adds another line below "[Created via email sent to: ... ]".

I would like to request that this be incorporated into future versions of Jira.

Here's the updated module code:

private String recordFromAddressForAnon(User reporter, Message message, String description) throws MessagingException
{
// If the message has been created for an anonymous user add the senders e-mail address to the description.
if (reporteruserName != null && reporteruserName.equals(reporter.getName()))
{
description += "\n[Created via e-mail ";
if (message.getFrom() != null && message.getFrom().length > 0)

{ description += "received from: " + message.getFrom()[0] + "]"; }
else

{ description += "but could not establish sender's address.]"; }
description += "\n[Created via email sent to: ";
if(message.getAllRecipients() != null && message.getAllRecipients().length > 0)
{
Address[] addresses = message.getAllRecipients();
for(int i=0; i < addresses.length; i++) { description += addresses[i] + " "; }
description += "]";
}
else
{ description += "but could not establish reciever's address(es).]"; }
} 
else
{
description += "\n[Created via email sent to: ";
if(message.getAllRecipients() != null && message.getAllRecipients().length > 0)
{
Address[] addresses = message.getAllRecipients();
for(int i=0; i < addresses.length; i++) { description += addresses[i] + " "; }	}
description += "]";
}
else

{ description += "but could not establish reciever's address(es).]"; }
}
return description;
}

